fields.description:
{panel}
In our [Confluence Documentation Directory|https://confluence.atlassian.com/alldoc/confluence-documentation-directory-12877996.html] docs, we mention that:
{quote}
We supply documentation for the latest version and previous versions of Confluence, in both online and offline (downloadable) form.
{quote}

However, we do not have cloud documentation in there.

Could we add exports of Confluence Cloud to this page as well? :)

Users are not able to search for terms like: 
{code}
will, there, and, as, if, for, with, on, it
{code}

The following message is displayed on Confluence:
{code}
The query could not be parsed
{code}

Workaround:

Search for these words with upper-case characters: Will, There, And, etc.

h3. Summary
The [User List Macro|https://confluence.atlassian.com/confcloud/user-list-macro-724765305.html] is no longer rendering and display a list of users from the groups specified. 

h3. Environment
* Cloud 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Edit a Confluence page and add the "User List" macro
# Specify any group or use an asterisk " * " for all groups
# Click on Preview

On a page with existing User List Macros:
# Navigate to Page and attempt to view Macro

h3. Expected Results
User List displays Users based on the Group(s) specified

h3. Actual Results
The Page displays the following error for the Macro:
{quote}Error rendering macro 'userlister' : null{quote}

From the JIRA Logs:
Viewing a Page with the User List Macro:
{noformat}
