h3. Summary

According to the [Confluence Search Syntax|https://confluence.atlassian.com/confcloud/confluence-search-syntax-724765423.html], we should be able to search for specific content, using different syntaxes. For example,  a wildcard search to find related words:
{quote}
chick*
{quote}

By trying to do the same operation for URLs, there will have no results. In an example for different URLs that start with https://na27 (shorter ones):
{quote}
https://na27*
{quote}


h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Go to the Confluence search, on the right side of the top bar
# Try to use syntaxes like wildcards and proximity searches

h3. Expected Results

Confluence should retrieve pages that include the content in the beginning of the URLs

h3. Actual Results
No results are displayed. Attached some examples.

h3.Workaround

{quote}
Just remove the :// from the search. For example: 
{code:java}
http*n27*
{code}
{quote}

h3. Summary
Pages that contains attachment displayed on them are timing out sometimes causing Confluence to crash (when export operation are running).

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Attempt to display a page which contains attachments.

h3. Expected Results
The page is displayed properly

